Description: Centralized system management server
 SysManage is a comprehensive system management platform that provides:
  * Centralized agent management
  * System monitoring and metrics
  * Package management across multiple systems
  * Security policy enforcement
  * Certificate management
  * Firewall configuration
  * User access control
  * Web-based administration interface
 .
 This package installs the SysManage server which manages connected
 agents. It requires a PostgreSQL database (can be on a separate host).
 .
 After installation, configure /etc/sysmanage.yaml to point to your
 PostgreSQL database. Use the online config builder at:
 https://sysmanage.org/config-builder.html

